text.tspan: The slope describes the change in the number of geolocated addresses per hexagon between two dates, divided by the length of the period. So, S = (Nht+1 - Nht)/δ(t), with Nh the

tspan.tspan: number of geolocated addresses in a hexagon. The space-normalized slope per period corresponds to the centered-scaled value, where the mean and standard deviation of slope are

text.tspan: calculated from the set of hexagons contained in the space for each period.
